SIMPLE: memorial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Memorial
<hw>Me*mo"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧morial</ets>, L. <ets>memorialis</ets>, fr.
<ets>memoria</ets>. See <er>Memory</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Serving to preserve remembrance; commemorative;
<as>as, a <ex>memorial</ex> building</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There high in air, <qex>memorial</qex> of my name,⟦br⟧
Fix the smooth oar, and bid me live to fame.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contained in memory; <as>as, a <ex>memorial</ex>
possession</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Mnemonic; assisting the memory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This succession of Aspirate, Soft, and Hard, may be expressed by
the <qex>memorial</qex> word ASH.</q> <rj><qau>Skeat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Memorial Day</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Memorial Day</er> in
the vocabulary. Also called <altname><er>Decoration
Day</er></altname>.</cd> <mark>[U.S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Memorial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Memorial
<hw>Me*mo"ri*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧morial</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Anything intended to
preserve the memory of a person or event; something which serves to keep
something else in remembrance; a monument.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Churches have names; some as <qex>memorials</qex> of peace, some
of wisdom, some in memory of the Trinity itself.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A memorandum; a record.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
R.]</mark> <rj><au>Hayward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A written representation of facts, addressed to the
government, or to some branch of it, or to a society, etc., -- often
accompanied with a petition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Memory; remembrance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Precious is the <qex>memorial</qex> of the just.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Diplomacy)</fld> <def>A species of informal state
paper, much used in negotiation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Memorial Day</ent>⟦br⟧
